Package: causalontology
Type: Package
Title: R Binding of the Causalontology Standard
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: person("AI University (AIU)", email = "ai.university.aiu@gmail.com",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: The R binding of the Causalontology standard: content-addressed
    identity over RFC 8785 (JSON Canonicalization Scheme) identity-bearing
    bytes with SHA-256, Ed25519 record-level signing and verification
    (RFC 8032), validation against the eight specification JSON Schemas,
    the thirteen semantic rules (temporal admissibility with fixed unit
    constants, the formal conflict test, refinement validity, hierarchy
    reachability, enrichment field and shape rules), and an in-memory
    conformant store with idempotent immutable puts, signed add-only
    provenance records with quarantine, materialized enrichment views with
    contributors, retraction and succession lineage, the resolve minimum,
    the deterministic cycle-breaking view rule, and the stigmergy gap read.
    Conformance is defined by the 38 vectors frozen at specification 1.0.0
    in the standard's repository; run conformance.R against them.
License: Apache License 2.0 | file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports: sodium, openssl
